==Cover versions and samples==
In 1996 British hip hop group Kaleef&#x27;s re-working of the song reached number 22 on the UK charts. The following year, a cover version by soul singer Omar reached number 37.

In 2007 British singer Jamelia released the single &quot;No More&quot;, which heavily samples &quot;Golden Brown&quot;.

In 2012 Cornwell sang a mariachi version of the song, backed by Mexican-British band Mariachi Mexteca (later known as the Mariachis).

In 2020 British YouTuber and saxophonist Laurence Mason&#x27;s cover of &quot;Golden Brown&quot; in the style of Dave Brubeck&#x27;s &quot;Take Five&quot; was viewed over a million times, leading to a commercial release via Amazon and iTunes and as a vinyl single under the title &quot;Take Vibe EP&quot;. The vinyl release stayed two weeks in the Official Vinyl Singles Chart&#x27;s Top 40, peaking at No 24. By 2025 the video had received more than 11 million views.

